For the seared salmon, heat the olive oil in a frying pan, season the salmon with salt and freshly ground black pepper and fry for 1-2 minutes on both sides, or until browned all over.For the sweet and sour peppers, heat the butter and oil in a frying pan, add the rest of the pepper ingredients and simmer for five minutes, or until the peppers are tender.To serve, spoon the peppers onto a serving plate and top with the salmon. Drizzle around some of the pan juices.